    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  The main protease, M\n                  <jats:sup>pro</jats:sup>\n                  , of SARS-CoV-2 is required to cleave the viral polyprotein into precise functional units for virus replication and pathogenesis. Here we demonstrate a quantitative reporter for M\n                  <jats:sup>pro</jats:sup>\n                  function in living cells, in which protease inhibition by genetic or chemical methods results in strong eGFP fluorescence. This robust gain-of-function system readily distinguishes between inhibitor potencies and can be scaled-up to high-throughput platforms for drug testing.\n                </jats:p>",
